> I  think we can deprecate 'filePath' and encourage to use 'fileUrl'. because fileUrl is more generic than filePath. keeping filePath is just for BC consideration.

Sure, I have removed separate admin-api for file-url and added to the same existing api.

@jerrypeng addressed comments.

@rdhabalia we need to either throw exceptions (like @srkukarni suggested) when topic pattern in specified for a python function or we need implement support for topic patterns within python functions

Update:

Just saw a previous comment about topic pattern being not available for python client.  In that case we should just throw an error when topic pattern is set when submitting a python function and later we can back fill this functionality
